HEADWORD: Nursling
<hw>Nurs"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Nurse</ets> +
<ets>-ling</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who, or that which, is nursed; an
infant; a fondling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I was his <qex>nursling</qex> once, and choice delight.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nurstle</ent>⟦br⟧
